om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Everything is securities fraud</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a U.S. senator interested i=
n foreign policy and concerned with the world=E2=80=99s perception of Israe=
l=E2=80=99s occupation of the Palestinian territories, there is really only=
 one thing you can do, which is write a letter to the Securities and Exchan=
ge Commission <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2627=
8571.277651/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZm94YnVzaW5lc3MuY29tL3BvbGl0aWNzL2dvcC1zZW5hdG9=
ycy1zZWMtaW52ZXN0aWdhdGUtdW5pbGV2ZXItYmVuLWplcnJ5cy1pc3JhZWwtYm95Y290dA/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB96354b68" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">raising some questions about securi=
ties fraud</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">GOP senators on=
 the Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs Committee have demanded answers fr=
om the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) on whether the parent compa=
ny of Ben &amp; Jerry=E2=80=99s has violated SEC rules in its Israel boycot=
t.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a December letter obtained excl=
usively by FOX Business to SEC Chairman Gary Gensler, Republican Sens. Thom=
 Tillis, of North Carolina, John Kennedy, of Louisiana, and Tim Scott, of S=
outh Carolina, called for an investigation into statements made by Unilever=
 following the Israeli-Palestinian conflict in July 2021.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On July 19, 2021, Ben &amp; Jerry=E2=80=99s announced =
it would no longer sell its ice cream in the "Occupied Palestinian Territor=
y," referring to the West Bank and Gaza Strip. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0Unilever back=
ed the move saying, "We also welcome the fact that Ben &amp; Jerry=E2=80=99=
s will stay in Israel," noted the lawmakers in their letter.</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">"There is strong reason to believe that these July 19 sta=
tements were knowingly and recklessly false," the GOP senators wrote, refer=
encing an Israeli law that prohibits targeted boycotts based on location.</=
p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is actually the second con=
gressional letter to the SEC about Palestinian-ice-cream-sales-based securi=
ties fraud that we have covered around here; back in November I <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26278571.277651/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMjkvYmlsbC1hY2ttYW4t=
aGFzLWEtc3BhcmM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEwNjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ=
1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMTA2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leX=
N0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB46f7abb1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote about</a> a congr=
essman who wants Unilever to update its risk factors, and now these guys wa=
nt Unilever investigated for its previous statements.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Do you think that they are worried about Unilever=E2=80=99=
s shareholders? About them being deceived? About Unilever doing a clever fr=
aud on those shareholders to induce them to buy Unilever stock by concealin=
g the fact that its Ben &amp; Jerry=E2=80=99s subsidiary=C2=A0<em>won=E2=80=
=99t=C2=A0</em>in fact be able to continue to sell ice cream in the non-Pal=
estinian parts of Israel?=C2=A0Come on.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The=
 point here is that =E2=80=9Ceverything is securities fraud=E2=80=9D is a w=
ay to=C2=A0<em>punish political speech.=C2=A0</em>In general, in the U.S., =
people =E2=80=94=C2=A0and also corporations =E2=80=94=C2=A0are allowed to e=
xpress their opinions about controversial political topics, and it is viewe=
d as unseemly for the government to punish them for doing so. And this is t=
rue even if they are factually mistaken, or outright lying: It is <em>bad=
=C2=A0</em>for people to lie about political matters, but the punishment fo=
r that is pretty much =E2=80=9Cjournalists might call you a liar=E2=80=9D; =
the government is not in the business of punishing even dishonest political=
 speech.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand it is illegal =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0it is securities fraud =E2=80=94=C2=A0for a company to lie t=
o its shareholders to get them to buy stock, and that rule is generally int=
erpreted broadly enough that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/26278571.277651/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDMvZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy1nb2VzLXRvLXN1cHJlbWUtY291cnQtaGV=
kZ2UtZnVuZHMtd29uLW9uLWdhbWVzdG9wLWtrcG9lNndzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMDYyMl9NT05FWV=
NUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyM=
DEwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8b182245" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;"> essentially any untrue statement</a> that a public company makes can=
 be called securities fraud.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So you j=
ust combine those two things and you can turn any sort of political speech =
or position-taking by a public corporation (or its executives, or its subsi=
diaries) into securities fraud. Find some debatable premise in what they sa=
y: fraud. Or, failing that, you can accuse them of fraud for failing to inc=
lude a risk factor about how their political position is actually bad, will=
 cost them customers, etc.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not new,=
 really; we=E2=80=99ve been talking about it around here since at least 201=
5, when New York=E2=80=99s attorney general <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/26278571.277651/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTUtMTEtMDYvZXh4b24tbWlnaHQtYmUtaW4tdHJvdWJsZS1v=
dmVyLWNsaW1hdGUtY2hhbmdlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMDYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW0=
9ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDEwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ2=
49bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB82ced223" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> accused Exxon =
Mobile Corp.</a> of securities fraud for lobbying against action on climate=
 change, and we=E2=80=99ve been talking about the letters-to-the-SEC versio=
n since 2016, when Senator Elizabeth Warren <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/26278571.277651/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTYtMDMtMzEvc2VuYXRvci1kb2Vzbi10LWxpa2UtY29tcGFu=
aWVzLWx5aW5nLXRvLWdvdmVybm1lbnQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEwNjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21=
lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMTA2JnV0bV9jYW=
1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB034aaac8" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> asked th=
e SEC to investigate</a> some brokerages for lobbying against a fiduciary-d=
uty rule. I do not believe that the New York attorney general was concerned=
 about Exxon=E2=80=99s shareholders, or that Elizabeth Warren was concerned=
 about those brokerages=E2=80=99 shareholders, or that these senators are c=
oncerned about Unilever=E2=80=99s shareholders. I believe that the sharehol=
ders are a useful pretext for the government to try to punish political spe=
ech.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This seems bad! To its credit,=C2=A0th=
e SEC seems to=C2=A0ignore=C2=A0these letters. Still!</p><table class=3D"li=
