=E2=80=9D would appear in =E2=80=9C<em>any</em> de-SPAC transaction=E2=80=
=9D and =E2=80=9Cwas not unique to the [a]cquisition.=E2=80=9D That this st=
ructure has been utilized by other SPACs does not cure it of conflicts.=C2=
=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know exact=
ly what this means for SPACs. One thing that it means is that if a SPAC doe=
s a deal and then the stock goes down, shareholders can sue in Delaware cou=
rt claiming that they were misinformed about the problems with the deal. Bu=
